  "text": "The Wrst homology modelling articles were published as early as the late 1970s [CITATION_1] , and since then we have kept using and improving the same concepts described in those ground-breaking articles. The process starts with the detection of a suitable template; an alignment is produced; insertions, deletions and residue substitutions are performed; the model is optimized; and since the late 1990s there is consensus that structure validation is needed to detect the unavoidable errors in the Wnal model.",
